Peacekeeping Workshop To Be Held In Zimbabwe 
A five-day international workshop to examine the conduct, practices and
principles of peacekeeping operations for military commanders and staff
will be held in Harare from January 23 to 27.
The workshop organized jointly by Zimbabwe and United Kingdom will draw
senior military officials from 19 African countries who have been
involved in peacekeeping operations, according to the local press.
A statement by the Zimbabwe National Army said on Thursday the workshop
was designed to provide guidance on training education requirements for
military commanders.
Zimbabwe's Defense Minister Moven Mahachi is expected to officially
open the workshop.
